# Project Structure Guide

This is a React TypeScript personal portfolio website for Dominic Kolbe.

## Key Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project configuration and dependencies
- [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Main React component
- [src/constants.ts](mdc:src/constants.ts) - Environment variables and app constants
- [src/assets/content.json](mdc:src/assets/content.json) - Content data for the portfolio
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [Taskfile.yml](mdc:Taskfile.yml) - Task automation for dependency updates

## Project Structure

- `src/` - Source code directory
  - `App.tsx` - Main application component
  - `constants.ts` - Environment and app constants
  - `assets/` - Static assets including content and fonts
  - `index.tsx` - Application entry point
- `public/` - Public assets served directly
- `.cursor/rules/` - Cursor IDE rules

## Technology Stack

- React 19.1.0 with TypeScript
- Emotion CSS for styling
- Vercel Analytics
- PNPM package manager
- Prettier for code formatting
